<center><font size=3D"+1"><b>Conversion Tables and Methods to Use when
converting</b></font>

<p><font size=3D"+1"><b>from Metric Units to Metric Units
(Volume)</b></font></p></center>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<center><font size=3D"+1"><b>Some terms to remember</b></font></center>

<p><table border=3D"1" cellspacing=3D"1" cellpadding=3D"7" width=3D"590">
   <tbody><tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"50%" height=3D"23">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1"><b>Meter =96
         Length</b></font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"50%" height=3D"23">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1"><b>Kilo =96
         Thousand</b></font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"50%" height=3D"23" bgcolor=3D"#FFFFFF">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1"><b>Liter =96
         Volume</b></font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"50%" height=3D"23">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1"><b>Milli =96
         Thousand</b></font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"50%" height=3D"23">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1"><b>Gram =96
         Mass/Weight</b></font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"50%" height=3D"23">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1"><b>Centi =96
         Hundred</b></font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"50%" height=3D"23">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <p><font size=3D"+1"><b>Celsius =96
         Temperature</b></font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"50%" height=3D"23">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <p><font size=3D"+1"><b>Deci =96 Ten</b></font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
</tbody></table>
</p>

<center><font size=3D"+1">&nbsp;</font></center>

<h3><center>Measure of Volumes</center></h3>

<p><table border=3D"1" cellspacing=3D"1" width=3D"623">
   <tbody><tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"38%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">10 <b>milliliters</b> (ml)
         =3D</font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"62%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1 <b>centiliter</b> (cl)</font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"38%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">10 <b>centiliters</b> =3D</font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"62%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1 <b>deciliter</b> (dl) =3D 100
         milliliters</font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"38%">
         <p><font size=3D"+1">1 <b>liter</b> =3D </font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"62%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1000 <b>milliliters</b></font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"38%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1 <b>milliliter</b> =3D </font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"62%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1 <b>cubic
         centimeter</b></font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"38%">
         <p><font size=3D"+1">1 <b>liter</b> =3D </font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"62%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1000 <b>cubic
         centimeters</b></font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"38%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">100 <b>centiliter</b> =3D</font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"62%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1 <b>liter</b> (L) =3D 1,000
         milliliters</font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"38%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1000 <b>liters</b> =3D</font></p>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"62%">
         <p>&nbsp;<font size=3D"+1">1 <b>kiloliter</b> (km)</font></p>
      </td>
   </tr>
</tbody></table>
</p>

<center><font size=3D"-1">&nbsp;</font></center>

<h3><center>Operations for Volume</center></h3>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><font size=3D"+1"><b>Example</b>: To get Milliliters from Liters you
Multiply the Liters by 1000</font></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><font size=3D"+1"><b>You Have</b>: 2 Liters</font></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><font size=3D"+1"><b>You want Cubic Centimeters</b>: <b>So, <u> </u>
Cubic Centimeters =3D <u> 23 </u>Liters</b></font></p>

<p><font size=3D"+1"><b>We Multiply the liters by 100</b>:
</font><font size=3D"-1"><img src=3D"https://mste.illinois.edu/dildine/tcd_=
files/metric/Image25.gif" width=3D"153" height=3D"20" align=3D"bottom"></fo=
nt></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><font size=3D"+1"><b>You want Cubic Centimeters</b>: <b>So, <u> </u>
Cubic Centimeters =3D <u> 23 </u>Liters </b></font>There are 2000
milliliters and 2000 Cucbic Centimeters (CCs) in 2 liters</p>

<p><table border=3D"1" cellspacing=3D"1" width=3D"636">
   <tbody><tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"31%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1"><b>If you have
         this</b></font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"40%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1"><b>Do this</b></font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"29%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1"><b>To get this</b></font></center>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"31%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">milliliters (ml) or
         CCs</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"40%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Divide by 10 (ml/10)
         </font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"29%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">centiliter (cl)</font></center>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"31%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">centiliters (cl)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"40%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Multiply by 10 (cl *
         10)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"29%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Milliliters (ml)</font></center>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"31%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Liters (L)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"40%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Multiply by 1000 (L *
         100)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"29%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Milliliters (mL) or
         CCs</font></center>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"31%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Liters (L)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"40%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Multiply by 100 (L *
         100)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"29%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Centiliters (cl)</font></center>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"31%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Centiliters (cl)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"40%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Divide by 100
         (cl/100)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"29%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Liters (L)</font></center>
      </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"31%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Milliliters (ml) or
         CCs</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"40%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Divide by 1000
         (ml/1000)</font></center>
      </td>
      <td valign=3D"top" width=3D"29%">
         <p>&nbsp;</p>
        =20
         <center><font size=3D"+1">Liters (L)</font></center>
      </td>
   </tr>
</tbody></table>
</p>

